<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/0> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 0 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "1. The path towards a regenerative economy: an integrated framework. From reverse logistics to closed-loop supply chains. Industrial symbiosis. The current social, political, economical and regulatory environment. Sin subniveles"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/1> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 1 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "2. Basics of circularity"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/10> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 10 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "3.5. others (non regulated sectors - yet- at EU level: textile, furniture, tyres, oil, ...) Sin subniveles"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/11> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 11 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "4. Servitization, sharing and product-service systems (PSS). Sharing economy and function-based economy Sin subniveles"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/12> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 12 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "5. Digitalization and circularity: technology for closing the loop Sin subniveles"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/13> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 13 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "6. Rethinking products, services and business models: circular design and the circular business model canvas. Biomimicry. Sin subniveles"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/14> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 14 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "7. Circular economy metrics Sin subniveles"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/15> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 15 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "8. Advanced topics in circular and regenerative economy Sin subniveles"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/2> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 2 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "2.1. Cradle-To-Cradle: technosphere and biosphere. Engineering regenerative and restorative supply chain processes. Sin subniveles"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/3> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 3 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "2.2. Product recovery options in a circular supply chain (technosphere): reuse/share; repair; refurbish; remanufacture; cannibalization; recycling. 11Rs. Connecting supply chains via repurposing for closing the loop. Sin subniveles"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53000689/2025-26/syllabus/4> a ns1:SyllabusItem ;
    ns1:itemIndex 4 ;
    ns1:syllabusDescription "2.3. Waste management. Separate collection and incentives. PAYT systems. MSW management and objectives. Sin subniveles"@es .

